                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=alexander",
                        "name": "alexander",
                        "displayName": "Alexander Veremyev",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Standard PDF fonts support only Latin1 encoding (actually some superset of Latin1 encoding).\nTo use non-Latin1 characters you have to use them with TTF fonts.\n\nSee [Using fonts|http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/manual\/en\/zend.pdf.drawing.html#zend.pdf.drawing.using-fonts] and [Standard PDF fonts limitations|http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/manual\/en\/zend.pdf.drawing.html#zend.pdf.drawing.standard-fonts-limitations] documentation sections for details.\n",
